originalText.text: This store racially profiles customers. If you are Black, based on my experiences, you are more than likely to be treated rudely and disrespectfully. When you complain to the manager, Winston, he just ignores. There needs to be a NEW management change here. I am not the only reviewer that has complained about a disparity in treatment based on race. This store at 1769 2nd Avenue gives the chain Keyfood a bad name.

originalText.text: I give Key Food one star (as opposed to zero) only because the employees and managers are great. They are very helpful and friendly. However, the store itself, and the products are awful, low quality, and at exorbitant prices. This store is significantly more expensive than the Whole Foods and the Health Food store in the area and the quality is much worse. As if that weren't enough, they sell expired items, such as old bread with mold. If you don't pay attention and check every single item microscopically, you discover after a day or two that the bread is old and has mold in it (which is not noticeable because the packaging is brown, as seen in the pictures I am sharing). It seems they get away with this because they are the only large supermarket in 2nd avenue. But it is worth to walk over to 3rd to either Food for Health (3rd Ave. between 92nd and 93rd) or Whole Foods (3rd Avenue and 87th).

originalText.text:
Very misleading promotional and sales campaign. Moreover, watch out, many times the advertised price is completely different than what you pay on the cash. The prices are not registered properly in the system. You need to keep an eye on the screen.

I am fed up being cheated on this store. Almost every time I discover new thing. Today I went to buy some groceries. I found coffee on sale with advertised price in big $5.99. I took two of them. Since I got stolen so many times before, I was scrutinizing the cashier screen and took photo of all the prices as advertised.

At the cashier, the coffee price became $7.99 and the second one was $13.99. The cashier explained that the price $5.99 is for the club card holder, and the offer is limited to only 1 item.

Please look at the advertised promotion photo that I took and juge for yourself.

Honestly I believe whoever is in charge of this store/promotions and manger should be fired on the spot for cheating their customers. Iâ€™ll never go back EVER. I am also going to file a complaint at the NY General Attorney Office website. SOOOO UNETHICAL PEOPLE

I did the mistake a come back to this place. Again another misleading pricing. The tag does not correspond to the items. Guys you need to get it together â€¦

Shame on you.
